{"kind":"project","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components"]}],"sections":[{"image":"ic_component_intro.png","projectFiles":"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"title":"Use your first OUDS components","chapter":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30,"backgroundImage":"ic_component_intro.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.2","kind":"hero"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"stepsSection":[{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-1.swift","runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"First, prepare the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContentView"},{"text":" by adding inside it a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollView"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add such picker with three items inside.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Now, let’s add radio buttons to let the user choose its gender.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The official components are ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadio"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadioItem"},{"text":", but the package has also a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadioPicker"},{"text":" to implement quicky a group of radios.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This component can be replaced by your own.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The radio picker is defined by an array of values to display radio items associated to a tag, i.e. an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" thing shared through a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Inside a picker the user can select only one value, not zero.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a checkbox item with only two states."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The radio picker is alone, it is the time to add below a checkbox. OUDS provides two components: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckbox"},{"text":" which is a simple checkbox, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckboxItem"},{"text":" which is a checkbox (duh!) with additional texts and icons.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The state of the checkbox is shared through a boolean ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"State"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In some cases you may need to use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},{"text":" if you want a three-states checkbox.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose to add an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are also components who do not have any behaviors and are here only for visual rendering, for example dividers which can be horizontal or vertical."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A divider is, in the end, a stroke with a color. You will see later, colors in OUDS have two values: a light mode value, and a dark mode value. Here the divider can have a color which can change, or not."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a switch item, it will be used as a trick to force the change of the color scheme for the view for our future operations."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You will then be able to see the automatic changes of colors when you switch the color scheme."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With radio and checkbox, OUDS provides also switch elements (toggles). They can be alone ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitch"},{"type":"text","text":") or with texts ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwitchItem"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Just like the checkbox, the switch exposes its state through a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" in the app and make it open the iOS documentation OUDS website."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users may need to navigate outside the app, like, for example, opening a website. Thus the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" component can be integrated. It can be only with a text or also a chevron indicator."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s add a button with some rules: if checkbox is not checked it is disabled. When tapped, change the style of the button during 5 seconds."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the end, we can also add a button. Button are one of the most used components in an app and bring a lof of the power and the style of the brand."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can find it with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":". Such button has an appearance changing its colors, and also a style (loading or not)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks to the theme, the enabled, disabled, hover, focus or pressed states are managed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"anchor":"Add-basic-components","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We will work on a kind of formular using main OUDS components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Feel free to style and design things as you want.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"title":"Add basic components"}]},{"assessments":[{"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Does the developer using OUDS component need to manage the look and feel of the components?","type":"text"}]}],"content":[],"choices":[{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No! The components use the design specifications, i.e. tokens, thanks to the theme, to define the style they must have in all cases."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the reason why the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" is so important: it injects the theme as environment variable so that any component can get it to define its style."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true}],"type":"multiple-choice"}],"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"kind":"callToAction","title":"Add more OUDS components","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components","type":"reference"},"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","abstract":[{"text":"Components can be similar to iOS native components, or can also be original and strongly related to Orange Unified Design System needs.","type":"text"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","category":"Orange Unified Design System","role":"project","title":"Use your first OUDS components"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","modules":[{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Preparation-of-the-theme"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components#Add-basic-components","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-use-first-components"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components#Add-basic-components","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Richer-and-more-original-components-of-OUDS"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Use-of-tokens","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Use-of-view-modifiers","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Final-result","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Want-to-be-an-artist","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-5-styling-things"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Typography,-view-modifiers-and-tokens"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-6-going-further#More-resources","kind":"task"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-6-going-further"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Go-further-with-more-ressources"}],"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/$volume","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS"]]},"references":{"tutorial-discovery-3-2.swift":{"fileType":"swift","content":["\/\/","\/\/ Software Name: OUDS iOS","\/\/ SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright (c) Orange SA","\/\/ SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT","\/\/","\/\/ This software is distributed under the MIT license,","\/\/ the text of which is available at https:\/\/opensource.org\/license\/MIT\/","\/\/ or see the \"LICENSE\" file for more details.","\/\/","\/\/ Authors: See CONTRIBUTORS.txt","\/\/ Software description: A SwiftUI components library with code examples for Orange Unified Design System","\/\/","","import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","struct ContentView: View {","","    @State var selectedGender: Genders = .male","","    var body: some View {","        OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selectedGender,","                        radios: genderRadioValues(),","                        placement: .horizontal(false))","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Utils","","    enum Genders: String, Hashable {","        case male","        case female","        case nonBinary","    }","","    func genderRadioValues() -> [OUDSRadioPickerData<Genders>] {","        [","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.male, label: \"Mr\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.female, label: \"Ms\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.nonBinary, label: \"Other\"),","        ]","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","fileName":"Content.swift","identifier":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.swift","highlights":[],"type":"file"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding":{"title":"Check Your Understanding","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Check Your Understanding","type":"text"}],"type":"link","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding"},"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip":{"type":"download","identifier":"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","url":"\/downloads\/OUDSThemesContract\/OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","checksum":"f8433d4159e30f165e4e030b78259f32cb24e25998a9b9b0b8637ed39e4d02d296daf8944aeba9a6f24f169d7d8b7c21e89614e2c53275489624f5d01479eb40"},"tutorial-discovery-3-1.swift":{"fileType":"swift","content":["import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","\/\/ MARK: - App","","@main","struct OUDSTutorialSandboxApp: App {","    ","    let myTheme = OrangeTheme()","    ","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: myTheme) {","                ContentView()","            }","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ MARK: - Tutorial Content View","","struct ContentView: View {","    ","    var body: some View {","        ScrollView {","            Text(\"Hello OUDSThemesContract!\")","        }","    }"],"syntax":"swift","fileName":"Tutorial.swift","identifier":"tutorial-discovery-3-1.swift","highlights":[{"line":25},{"line":26},{"line":27}],"type":"file"},"tutorial-discovery-3-7.swift":{"fileType":"swift","content":["\/\/","\/\/ Software Name: OUDS iOS","\/\/ SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright (c) Orange SA","\/\/ SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT","\/\/","\/\/ This software is distributed under the MIT license,","\/\/ the text of which is available at https:\/\/opensource.org\/license\/MIT\/","\/\/ or see the \"LICENSE\" file for more details.","\/\/","\/\/ Authors: See CONTRIBUTORS.txt","\/\/ Software description: A SwiftUI components library with code examples for Orange Unified Design System","\/\/","","import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","struct ContentView: View {","","    @State var selectedGender: Genders = .male","    @State var termsAccepted: Bool = false","    @State var switchToDarkMode: Bool = false","    @State var creatingProfile: Bool = false","","    @Environment(\\.openURL) var openUrl","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selectedGender,","                            radios: genderRadioValues(),","                            placement: .horizontal(false))","","            OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","","            OUDSCheckboxItem(\"I accept the terms of use\", isOn: $termsAccepted)","","            OUDSSwitchItem(\"Switch to dark mode\", isOn: $switchToDarkMode)","","            OUDSLink(text: \"Go to the website\", indicator: .next) {","                openUrl.callAsFunction(URL(string: \"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\")!)","            }","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Create my profile\",","                       appearance: .strong,","                       style: creatingProfile ? .loading : .default)","            {","                creatingProfile = true","                DispatchQueue.main.asyncAfter(deadline: .now() + 5) {","                    creatingProfile = false","                }","            }.disabled(!termsAccepted)","        }.preferredColorScheme(switchToDarkMode ? .dark : .light)","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Utils","","    enum Genders: String, Hashable {","        case male","        case female","        case nonBinary","    }","","    func genderRadioValues() -> [OUDSRadioPickerData<Genders>] {","        [","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.male, label: \"Mr\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.female, label: \"Ms\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.nonBinary, label: \"Other\"),","        ]","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","fileName":"Content.swift","identifier":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.swift","highlights":[{"line":22},{"line":41},{"line":42},{"line":43},{"line":44},{"line":45},{"line":46},{"line":47},{"line":48},{"line":49},{"line":50}],"type":"file"},"tutorial-discovery-3-6.swift":{"fileType":"swift","content":["\/\/","\/\/ Software Name: OUDS iOS","\/\/ SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright (c) Orange SA","\/\/ SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT","\/\/","\/\/ This software is distributed under the MIT license,","\/\/ the text of which is available at https:\/\/opensource.org\/license\/MIT\/","\/\/ or see the \"LICENSE\" file for more details.","\/\/","\/\/ Authors: See CONTRIBUTORS.txt","\/\/ Software description: A SwiftUI components library with code examples for Orange Unified Design System","\/\/","","import OUDSSwiftUI","import SwiftUI","","struct ContentView: View {","","    @State var selectedGender: Genders = .male","    @State var termsAccepted: Bool = false","    @State var switchToDarkMode: Bool = false","","    @Environment(\\.openURL) var openUrl","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            OUDSRadioPicker(selection: $selectedGender,","                            radios: genderRadioValues(),","                            placement: .horizontal(false))","","            OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","","            OUDSCheckboxItem(\"I accept the terms of use\", isOn: $termsAccepted)","","            OUDSSwitchItem(\"Switch to dark mode\", isOn: $switchToDarkMode)","","            OUDSLink(text: \"Go to the website\", indicator: .next) {","                openUrl.callAsFunction(URL(string: \"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\")!)","            }","        }.preferredColorScheme(switchToDarkMode ? .dark : .light)","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Utils","","    enum Genders: String, Hashable {","        case male","        case female","        case nonBinary","    }","","    func genderRadioValues() -> [OUDSRadioPickerData<Genders>] {","        [","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.male, label: \"Mr\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.female, label: \"Ms\"),","            OUDSRadioPickerData(tag: Genders.nonBinary, label: \"Other\"),","        ]","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","fileName":"Content.swift","identifier":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.swift","highlights":[{"line":23},{"line":24},{"line":36},{"line":37},{"line":38},{"line":39}],"type":"file"},"tutorial-discovery-3-6.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.png","alt":"A radio picker, an horizontal divider, a checkbox item, a switch item and a link","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-3-6.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app":{"url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything.","type":"text"}],"kind":"section","title":"Basic structure for the app","role":"pseudoSymbol"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)":{"kind":"overview","url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents-(discovery)","abstract":[{"text":"Discovering a new framework can be exciting and scary. Learn how you can embed and use OUDS Swift Package.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"With this tutorial you will learn fundamental concepts of Orange Unified Design System and discover the layers of this framework.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Theme, components, tokens… everything will be introduced!","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift Package Discovery Tutorial","type":"topic","role":"overview","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS":{"url":"\/tutorials\/table-of-contents-(discovery)\/use-of-first-components-provided-by-ouds","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS","type":"topic","abstract":[],"kind":"article","title":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","role":"article"},"doc://OUDSThemesContract/tutorials/OUDSThemesContract/tutorial-discovery-6-going-further":{"kind":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-6-going-further","abstract":[{"text":"Since you have learned how OUDS works with theme, themeable view, components, tuning and view modifiers, it is time now to discover some online resources.","type":"text"}],"title":"Going further with more resources","type":"topic","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-6-going-further"},"doc://OUDSThemesContrac